overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request with numerous
  issues, including critical security vulnerabilities and breaking Vercel
  deploys. The assistant systematically addressed these concerns. It started by
  fixing local lint errors that were preventing successful builds. The core
  security fix involved replacing an easily forgeable 'true' cookie with a
  robust HMAC-signed session management system for admin authentication,
  impacting login, logout, and middleware. Additionally, API routes for
  responses and CSV export were secured with parameter validation and pagination
  limits to prevent abuse and memory exhaustion. Several bugs were resolved,
  such as incorrect PDF calculations for sleep metrics (now including minutes
  and handling empty inputs), allowing null values in number fields, wiring up
  the PDF download button, and replacing hardcoded user names in reports.
  Finally, regex validation was added for time fields in the Zod schema. All
  changes were committed and pushed, and a local build confirmed the fixes. A
  potential Edge Runtime compatibility issue with the  module in the
  middleware was identified, with a plan to configure the middleware to use
  Node.js runtime.
